{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:job.32",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 32,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 32",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 32 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:job.32.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:1",
      "text": "So these three men ceased to answer Job, because he seemed just to himself.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.32.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:2",
      "text": "And Eliu the son of Barachel the Buzite of the kindred of Ram, was angry and was moved to indignation: now he was angry against Job, because he said he was just before God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.32.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:3",
      "text": "And he was angry with his friends, because they had not found a reasonable answer, but only had condemned Job.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.32.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:4",
      "text": "So Eliu waited while Job was speaking because they were his elders that were speaking.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.32.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:5",
      "text": "But when he saw that the three were not able to answer, he was exceedingly angry.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.32.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:6",
      "text": "Then Eliu the son of Barachel the Buzite answered, and said: I am younger in days, and you are more ancient, therefore hanging down my head, I was afraid to shew you my opinion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.32.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:7",
      "text": "For I hoped that greater age would speak, and that a multitude of years would teach wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.32.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:8",
      "text": "But, as I see, there is a spirit in men, and the inspiration of the Almighty giveth understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.32.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:9",
      "text": "They that are aged are not the wise men, neither do the ancients understand judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.32.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:10",
      "text": "Therefore I will speak: Hearken to me, I also will shew you my wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.32.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:11",
      "text": "For I have waited for your words, I have given ear to your wisdom, as long as you were disputing in words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.32.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:12",
      "text": "And as long as I thought you said some thing, I considered: but, as I see, there is none of you that can convince Job, and answer his words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.32.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:13",
      "text": "Lest you should say: We have found wisdom, God hath cast him down, not man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.32.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:14",
      "text": "He hath spoken nothing to me, and I will not answer him according to your words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.32.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:15",
      "text": "They were afraid, and answered no more, and they left off speaking.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.32.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:16",
      "text": "Therefore because I have waited, and they have not spoken: they stood, and answered no more:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.32.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:17",
      "text": "I also will answer my part, and will shew my knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.32.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:18",
      "text": "For I am full of matter to speak of, and the spirit of my bowels straiteneth me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.32.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:19",
      "text": "Behold, my belly is as new wine which wanteth vent, which bursteth the new vessels.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.32.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:20",
      "text": "I will speak and take breath a little: I will open my lips, and will answer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.32.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:21",
      "text": "I will not accept the person of man, and I will not level God with man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.32.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:22",
      "text": "For I know not how long I shall continue, and whether after a while my Maker may take me away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
